    "comment": "Rationale: Figure 1: Immunofluorescence and immunogold-EM imaging of cerebella from wildtype and knockout mice showed monoacylglycerol lipase (aka. MGL, gene MGLL) was localized to parallel fiber presynaptic terminals, absent in other synaptic terminals and weakly localized to Bergman glia.. Experimental description: Result section, describing that mice were used in immuno EM: \"The density of MGL labeling was calculated as the mean number of metal particles per 1 μm2 of each element in wild-type and global MGL-KO mice. Statistically significant MGL labeling was found only in PF terminals and the BG (Fig. 1H).\"\n\nMGL antibody was produced at PMID:21613483\n\"For production of the MGL antibody, a cDNA fragment encoding the N-terminal 35 amino acids (NCBI reference sequence NM_011844) was subcloned into BamHI/EcoRI site of pGEX4T-2 plasmid (GE Healthcare) for expression of glutathione S-transferase fusion proteins.\"",
